This project is an original implementation informed by the design ideas in:

  - huashu-info-search, by Huashu: multi-channel technology research,
    freshness awareness, source attribution, and knowledge capture.
  - huashu-research, by Huashu: create the research record before searching,
    save incrementally, separate research from drafting, and report gaps.
  - xhs-writer-skill/references/reference-search.md, by JuneYaooo:
    multi-angle bilingual search, original-page acquisition, independent
    corroboration, and a writing-oriented source handoff.
    Repository: https://github.com/JuneYaooo/xhs-writer-skill
    Reviewed source commit: 6adef3b97db63dd931a1fd6b29550b31832355bd
    Upstream license: Apache License 2.0.
  - Agent Reach: anonymous public-channel routing patterns for web, RSS,
    GitHub, V2EX, YouTube, and Bilibili research.
  - url-to-markdown: public rendered-page capture and Hacker News source
    extraction boundaries.
  - content-research-writer: the boundary between source evaluation and
    downstream drafting.

No source code, templates, or verbatim workflow text from those projects is
included. All instructions, schemas, tests, and repository files in this
distribution were written for collect-sources and are licensed under the MIT
License in LICENSE.

The installable Skill is packaged under collect-sources/ so its references,
metadata, license, and notice travel together. Repository documentation,
tests, and CI remain at the repository root; exact copies of LICENSE and
NOTICE are bundled inside the installable Skill.
